Garanti, Sabanci, Turkish Airlines: Turkish Equity Preview

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-06-30T06:38:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/garanti-sabanci-turkish-airlines-turkish-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 Index (XU100)  rose 183.80, or
0.3 percent, to 63,002.88 yesterday.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  :  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA (BBVA)  wants a controlling stake in Turkey’s largest
listed lender, Expansion reported, citing BBVA President Angel Cano. The Spanish bank already owns 24.9 percent of Garanti and
will increase its holding over the next two or three years to
gain control, the newspaper said. Garanti fell 6 kurus, or 0.8
percent, to 7.34 liras yesterday.  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  : The winning
bidders in power grid tenders are required to make an extra down
payment to the Privatization Administration today. Enerjisa, a
joint venture between Sabanci Holding and  Verbund AG (VER) , was
invited to purchase the Akdeniz grid after Park Holding
withdrew. Sabanci lost 4 kurus, or 0.6 percent, to 6.86 liras.  Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO: The national carrier known
as Turkish Airlines had its price estimate cut to 4.9 liras per
share at Morgan Stanley, which cited higher oil prices and a
declining load factor in an e-mailed report today. The shares
dropped 5 kurus, or 1.2 percent, to 4.23 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
